            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Developed a pneumatic robotic pillow that achieves non-invasive snoring mitigation by precisely controlling balloon height using Poiseuille-based flow modeling and dual barometers instead of a flow meter. Leveraging only the built-in pressure sensors, the system extracts breathing and heart-rate signals via frequency analysis and uses a Transformer–CNN multi-task network to jointly recognize posture, snoring, and apnea events for closed-loop sleep intervention.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-500 mb-4">
